[
    [
        {
            "type": "header",
            "bbox": [
                0.255,
                0.07,
                0.684,
                0.087
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "S.-T. Yau College Student Mathematics Contests 2020"
        },
        {
            "type": "title",
            "bbox": [
                0.259,
                0.107,
                0.681,
                0.128
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "Computational and Applied Mathematics"
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "bbox": [
                0.392,
                0.136,
                0.544,
                0.152
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "Solve every problem."
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "bbox": [
                0.112,
                0.174,
                0.826,
                0.21
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "Problem 1. Let \\( f \\in C^{k+1}[-1,1] \\) and \\([-1,1]\\) be partitioned into subintervals \\( I_j = [(j-1)h,jh] \\) of width \\( h \\). Assume \\( p \\) is a polynomial of degree \\( k \\) which approximates \\( f \\) in \\( I_j \\) with"
        },
        {
            "type": "equation",
            "bbox": [
                0.36,
                0.227,
                0.577,
                0.255
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "\\[\n\\max  _ {x \\in I _ {j}} \\left| p _ {j} (x) - f (x) \\right| \\leq C _ {0} h ^ {k + 1},\n\\]"
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "bbox": [
                0.112,
                0.274,
                0.825,
                0.307
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "where \\( C_0 \\) is a constant independent of \\( j \\). Show that there exists an another constant \\( C \\), independent of \\( j \\), such that"
        },
        {
            "type": "equation",
            "bbox": [
                0.36,
                0.307,
                0.577,
                0.334
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "\\[\n\\max  _ {x \\in I _ {j \\pm 1}} \\left| p _ {j} (x) - f (x) \\right| \\leq C h ^ {k + 1}.\n\\]"
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "bbox": [
                0.113,
                0.35,
                0.382,
                0.368
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "(as long as \\(I_{j\\pm 1}\\subset [-1,1]\\) , of course)."
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "bbox": [
                0.112,
                0.39,
                0.499,
                0.405
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "Solution: Pick points \\(0 \\leq x_0 < x_1 < \\dots < x_k \\leq 1\\), and let"
        },
        {
            "type": "equation",
            "bbox": [
                0.403,
                0.411,
                0.534,
                0.445
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "\\[\nL _ {i} (x) = \\prod_ {l \\neq i} \\frac {x - x _ {l}}{x _ {i} - x _ {l}}\n\\]"
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "bbox": [
                0.113,
                0.452,
                0.361,
                0.466
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "be the \\(l\\)-th Lagrange polynomial. Let"
        },
        {
            "type": "equation",
            "bbox": [
                0.388,
                0.466,
                0.548,
                0.507
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "\\[\n\\Lambda = \\sum_ {i = 0} ^ {k} \\max  _ {x \\in [ - 1, 2 ]} | L _ {i} (x) |.\n\\]"
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "bbox": [
                0.113,
                0.51,
                0.519,
                0.526
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "On \\(I_{j}\\) we use rescaled versions with \\(x_{ji} = (j - 1)h + hx_{i}\\), and"
        },
        {
            "type": "equation",
            "bbox": [
                0.392,
                0.532,
                0.545,
                0.567
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "\\[\nL _ {j i} (x) = \\prod_ {l \\neq i} \\frac {x - x _ {j l}}{x _ {j i} - x _ {j l}}.\n\\]"
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "bbox": [
                0.113,
                0.574,
                0.316,
                0.588
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "Note that \\(\\Lambda\\) is unchanged with"
        },
        {
            "type": "equation",
            "bbox": [
                0.39,
                0.586,
                0.547,
                0.618
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "\\[\n\\Lambda = \\sum_ {i} \\max  _ {x \\in L _ {j \\pm 1}} \\left| L _ {j i} (x) \\right|.\n\\]"
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "bbox": [
                0.113,
                0.622,
                0.402,
                0.637
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "Let \\( f_{j} \\) be the interpolating polynomial on \\( I_{j} \\)"
        },
        {
            "type": "equation",
            "bbox": [
                0.386,
                0.646,
                0.551,
                0.685
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "\\[\nf _ {j} (x) = \\sum_ {i = 0} ^ {k} f \\left(x _ {j i}\\right) L _ {j i} (x),\n\\]"
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "bbox": [
                0.113,
                0.694,
                0.234,
                0.707
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "and note that also"
        },
        {
            "type": "equation",
            "bbox": [
                0.385,
                0.704,
                0.552,
                0.735
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "\\[\np _ {j} (x) = \\sum_ {i} p (x _ {j i}) L _ {j i} (x).\n\\]"
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "bbox": [
                0.113,
                0.739,
                0.235,
                0.754
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "Then for \\(x\\in I_{j\\pm 1}\\)"
        },
        {
            "type": "equation",
            "bbox": [
                0.244,
                0.761,
                0.695,
                0.922
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "\\[\n\\begin{array}{l} \\left| p _ {j} (x) - f (x) \\right| \\leq \\left| p _ {j} (x) - f _ {j} (x) \\right| + \\left| f _ {j} (x) - f (x) \\right| \\\\ = \\left| \\sum_ {i = 0} ^ {k} \\left(f \\left(x _ {j i}\\right) - p _ {j} \\left(x _ {j i}\\right) L _ {j i} (x) \\right. \\right\\rvert + \\left| R _ {k} f (x) \\right| \\\\ \\leq \\max  _ {x \\in I _ {j}} | f (x) - p _ {j} (x) | \\Lambda + \\frac {\\| f ^ {(k + 1)} \\|}{(k + 1) !} \\max  _ {x \\in I _ {j \\pm 1}} \\left| \\prod_ {i = 0} ^ {k} (x - x _ {j i}) \\right| \\\\ \\leq C _ {0} \\Lambda h ^ {k + 1} + \\frac {\\| f ^ {(k + 1)} \\|}{(k + 1) !} \\max  _ {x} | (2 h) ^ {k + 1} | \\\\ = C h ^ {k + 1}, \\\\ \\end{array}\n\\]"
        }
    ],
    [
        {
            "type": "equation",
            "bbox": [
                0.381,
                0.066,
                0.559,
                0.101
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "\\[\nC = C _ {0} \\Lambda + \\frac {2 ^ {k + 1} \\| f ^ {(k + 1)} \\|}{(k + 1) !}.\n\\]"
        },
        {
            "type": "title",
            "bbox": [
                0.113,
                0.128,
                0.373,
                0.143
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "Problem 2. Consider the iteration"
        },
        {
            "type": "equation",
            "bbox": [
                0.339,
                0.16,
                0.602,
                0.199
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "\\[\nx _ {n + 1} = x _ {n} - \\left(\\frac {x _ {n} - x _ {0}}{f (x _ {n}) - f (x _ {0})}\\right) f (x _ {n})\n\\]"
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "bbox": [
                0.112,
                0.215,
                0.827,
                0.25
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "for finding the roots of a two times continuous differentiable function \\( f(x) \\). Assuming the method converges to a simple root \\( x^* \\), what is the rate of convergence? Justify your answer."
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "bbox": [
                0.112,
                0.27,
                0.405,
                0.286
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "Solution: The iteration may be rewritten as"
        },
        {
            "type": "equation",
            "bbox": [
                0.222,
                0.291,
                0.717,
                0.326
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "\\[\nx _ {n + 1} = \\frac {[ x _ {n} f (x _ {n}) - x _ {n} f (x _ {0}) ] - [ x _ {n} f (x _ {n}) - x _ {0} f (x _ {n}) ]}{f (x _ {n}) - f (x _ {0})} = \\frac {x _ {0} f (x _ {n}) - x _ {n} f (x _ {0})}{f (x _ {n}) - f (x _ {0})}.\n\\]"
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "bbox": [
                0.113,
                0.33,
                0.153,
                0.344
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "Thus"
        },
        {
            "type": "equation",
            "bbox": [
                0.227,
                0.34,
                0.711,
                0.373
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "\\[\nx _ {n + 1} - x ^ {*} = \\frac {x _ {0} f (x _ {n}) - x _ {n} f (x _ {0})}{f (x _ {n}) - f (x _ {0})} - x ^ {*} = \\frac {(x _ {0} - x ^ {*}) f (x _ {n}) - (x _ {n} - x ^ {*}) f (x _ {0})}{f (x _ {n}) - f (x _ {0})}.\n\\]"
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "bbox": [
                0.113,
                0.376,
                0.57,
                0.391
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "Taylor's Theorem asserts that there is \\(\\xi_{n}\\) between \\(x_{n}\\) and \\(x^{*}\\) such that"
        },
        {
            "type": "equation",
            "bbox": [
                0.235,
                0.398,
                0.701,
                0.416
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "\\[\n0 = f \\left(x ^ {*}\\right) = f \\left(x _ {n}\\right) + f ^ {\\prime} \\left(\\xi_ {n}\\right) \\left(x ^ {*} - x _ {n}\\right) \\quad \\Rightarrow \\quad f \\left(x _ {n}\\right) = f ^ {\\prime} \\left(\\xi_ {n}\\right) \\left(x _ {n} - x ^ {*}\\right).\n\\]"
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "bbox": [
                0.113,
                0.423,
                0.201,
                0.438
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "This implies"
        },
        {
            "type": "equation",
            "bbox": [
                0.314,
                0.435,
                0.625,
                0.468
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "\\[\nx _ {n + 1} - x ^ {*} = \\frac {(x _ {0} - x ^ {*}) f ^ {\\prime} (\\xi_ {n}) - f (x _ {0})}{f (x _ {n}) - f (x _ {0})} (x _ {n} - x ^ {*}).\n\\]"
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "bbox": [
                0.113,
                0.471,
                0.411,
                0.486
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "Evaluating the limit as \\(n\\to \\infty\\) \\(\\xi_{n}\\rightarrow x^{*}\\) and"
        },
        {
            "type": "equation",
            "bbox": [
                0.18,
                0.492,
                0.757,
                0.527
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "\\[\n\\lim _ {n \\to \\infty} \\left| \\frac {x _ {n + 1} - x ^ {*}}{x _ {n} - x ^ {*}} \\right| = \\lim _ {n \\to \\infty} \\left| \\frac {(x _ {0} - x ^ {*}) f ^ {\\prime} (\\xi_ {n}) - f (x _ {0})}{f (x ^ {*}) - f (x _ {0})} \\right| = \\left| \\frac {(x _ {0} - x ^ {*}) \\lim _ {n \\to \\infty} f ^ {\\prime} (\\xi_ {n}) - f (x _ {0})}{0 - f (x _ {0})} \\right|.\n\\]"
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "bbox": [
                0.113,
                0.532,
                0.725,
                0.548
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "Applying Taylor's expression one more time, we know there is \\(\\eta\\) between \\(x^{*}\\) and \\(x_0\\) such that"
        },
        {
            "type": "equation",
            "bbox": [
                0.297,
                0.554,
                0.644,
                0.583
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "\\[\nf (x _ {0}) = f (x ^ {*}) + f ^ {\\prime} (x ^ {*}) (x _ {0} - x ^ {*}) + \\frac {f ^ {\\prime \\prime} (\\eta)}{2} (x _ {0} - x ^ {*}) ^ {2},\n\\]"
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "bbox": [
                0.113,
                0.59,
                0.137,
                0.602
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "So"
        },
        {
            "type": "equation",
            "bbox": [
                0.318,
                0.599,
                0.62,
                0.63
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "\\[\nf ^ {\\prime} \\left(x ^ {*}\\right) \\left(x _ {0} - x ^ {*}\\right) - f \\left(x _ {0}\\right) = - \\frac {f ^ {\\prime \\prime} (\\eta)}{2} \\left(x _ {0} - x ^ {*}\\right) ^ {2}.\n\\]"
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "bbox": [
                0.113,
                0.632,
                0.183,
                0.645
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "Therefore"
        },
        {
            "type": "equation",
            "bbox": [
                0.339,
                0.641,
                0.599,
                0.676
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "\\[\n\\lim  _ {n \\rightarrow \\infty} \\left| \\frac {x _ {n + 1} - x ^ {*}}{x _ {n} - x ^ {*}} \\right| = \\left| \\frac {f ^ {\\prime \\prime} (\\eta)}{2 f (x _ {0})} \\right| (x _ {0} - x ^ {*}) ^ {2}.\n\\]"
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "bbox": [
                0.112,
                0.678,
                0.827,
                0.711
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "Note the right hand side is dependent only upon \\( x^{*} \\) and \\( x_0 \\). Since we know \\( x_{n}\\to x^{*} \\), this shows the rate of convergence is linear."
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "bbox": [
                0.112,
                0.724,
                0.828,
                0.81
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "Problem 3. Suppose \\(\\mathbf{A}\\) is an \\(m \\times m\\) matrix with a complete set of orthonormal eigenvectors \\(\\mathbf{q}_1, \\ldots, \\mathbf{q}_m\\) and corresponding eigenvalues \\(\\lambda_1, \\ldots, \\lambda_m\\). Assume that \\(|\\lambda_1| > |\\lambda_2| > |\\lambda_3|\\) and \\(\\lambda_j \\geq \\lambda_{j+1}\\) for \\(j = 3, \\ldots, m\\). Consider the power method \\(\\mathbf{v}^{(k)} = \\mathbf{A}\\mathbf{v}^{(k-1)} / \\lambda_1\\), with \\(\\mathbf{v}^{(0)} = \\alpha_1\\mathbf{q}_1 + \\dots + \\alpha_m\\mathbf{q}_m\\) where \\(\\alpha_1\\) and \\(\\alpha_2\\) are both nonzero. Show that the sequence \\(\\{\\mathbf{v}^{(k)}\\}_{k=0}^{\\infty}\\) converges linearly to \\(\\alpha_1\\mathbf{q}_1\\) with asymptotic constant \\(C = |\\lambda_2 / \\lambda_1|\\)."
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "bbox": [
                0.112,
                0.831,
                0.482,
                0.847
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "Solution: Matrix A has following eigen-decomposition"
        },
        {
            "type": "equation",
            "bbox": [
                0.266,
                0.853,
                0.674,
                0.926
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "\\[\n\\mathbf {A} = \\left[ \\mathbf {q} _ {1}, \\mathbf {q} _ {2}, \\dots , \\mathbf {q} _ {m} \\right] \\left[ \\begin{array}{c c c c} \\lambda_ {1} & & & \\\\ & \\lambda_ {2} & & \\\\ & & \\ddots & \\\\ & & & \\lambda_ {m} \\end{array} \\right] \\left[ \\mathbf {q} _ {1}, \\mathbf {q} _ {2}, \\dots , \\mathbf {q} _ {m} \\right] ^ {- 1},\n\\]"
        }
    ],
    [
        {
            "type": "text",
            "bbox": [
                0.114,
                0.072,
                0.147,
                0.085
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "thus"
        },
        {
            "type": "equation",
            "bbox": [
                0.26,
                0.089,
                0.677,
                0.164
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "\\[\n\\mathbf {A} ^ {k} = \\left[ \\mathbf {q} _ {1}, \\mathbf {q} _ {2}, \\dots , \\mathbf {q} _ {m} \\right] \\left[ \\begin{array}{c c c c} \\lambda_ {1} ^ {k} & & & \\\\ & \\lambda_ {2} ^ {k} & & \\\\ & & \\ddots & \\\\ & & & \\lambda_ {m} ^ {k} \\end{array} \\right] \\left[ \\mathbf {q} _ {1}, \\mathbf {q} _ {2}, \\dots , \\mathbf {q} _ {m} \\right] ^ {- 1}.\n\\]"
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "bbox": [
                0.114,
                0.168,
                0.313,
                0.182
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "The power method reduces to"
        },
        {
            "type": "equation",
            "bbox": [
                0.189,
                0.187,
                0.748,
                0.358
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "\\[\n\\begin{array}{l} \\mathbf {v} ^ {(k)} = \\mathbf {A} ^ {k} \\frac {\\mathbf {v} ^ {(0)}}{\\lambda_ {1} ^ {k}} \\\\ = \\left[ \\mathbf {q} _ {1}, \\mathbf {q} _ {2}, \\dots , \\mathbf {q} _ {m} \\right] \\left[ \\begin{array}{c c c c} \\lambda_ {1} ^ {k} & & & \\\\ & \\lambda_ {2} ^ {k} & & \\\\ & & \\ddots & \\\\ & & & \\lambda_ {m} ^ {k} \\end{array} \\right] \\left[ \\begin{array}{c} \\mathbf {q} _ {1}, \\mathbf {q} _ {2}, \\dots , \\mathbf {q} _ {m} \\end{array} \\right] ^ {- 1} \\left[ \\begin{array}{c} \\mathbf {q} _ {1}, \\mathbf {q} _ {2}, \\dots , \\mathbf {q} _ {m} \\end{array} \\right] \\left[ \\begin{array}{c} \\frac {\\alpha_ {1}}{\\lambda_ {1} ^ {k}} \\\\ \\frac {\\alpha_ {2}}{\\lambda_ {1} ^ {k}} \\\\ \\vdots \\\\ \\frac {\\alpha_ {m}}{\\lambda_ {1} ^ {k}}, \\end{array} \\right] \\\\ = \\alpha_ {1} \\mathbf {q} _ {1} + \\sum_ {j = 2} ^ {m} \\left(\\frac {\\lambda_ {j}}{\\lambda_ {1}}\\right) ^ {k} \\alpha_ {j} \\mathbf {q} _ {j}, \\\\ \\end{array}\n\\]"
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "bbox": [
                0.113,
                0.364,
                0.639,
                0.382
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "from this we deduce \\(\\mathbf{v}^{(k)}\\to \\alpha_{1}\\mathbf{q}_{1}\\) as \\(k\\rightarrow \\infty\\) , since \\(|\\lambda_j / \\lambda_1| < 1\\) for \\(j = 2,\\ldots ,m\\)"
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "bbox": [
                0.113,
                0.388,
                0.772,
                0.405
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "To show the convergence is linear with asymptotic constant \\( C = |\\lambda_2 / \\lambda_1| \\) we need to verify the limit"
        },
        {
            "type": "equation",
            "bbox": [
                0.189,
                0.41,
                0.748,
                0.446
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "\\[\n\\lim  _ {k \\rightarrow \\infty} \\frac {\\left|\\left| e ^ {(k + 1)} \\right|\\right|}{\\left|\\left| e ^ {(k)} \\right|\\right|} = \\lim  _ {k \\rightarrow \\infty} \\frac {\\left|\\left| \\mathbf {v} ^ {(k + 1)} - \\alpha_ {1} \\mathbf {q} _ {1} \\right|\\right|}{\\left|\\left| \\mathbf {v} ^ {(k)} - \\alpha_ {1} \\mathbf {q} _ {1} \\right|\\right|} = \\left| \\frac {\\lambda_ {2}}{\\lambda_ {1}} \\right| \\quad (\\text {h e r e} | | \\cdot | | d e n o t e s t h e L _ {2} - n o r m).\n\\]"
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "bbox": [
                0.113,
                0.451,
                0.689,
                0.479
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "Note that \\( e^{(k)} = \\sum_{j=2}^{m} \\left( \\frac{\\lambda_j}{\\lambda_1} \\right)^k \\alpha_j \\mathbf{q}_j \\), using the orthonormality of the eigenvectors we have"
        },
        {
            "type": "equation",
            "bbox": [
                0.266,
                0.485,
                0.672,
                0.532
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "\\[\n| | e ^ {(k)} | | ^ {2} = \\sum_ {j = 2} ^ {m} \\left| \\frac {\\lambda_ {j}}{\\lambda_ {1}} \\right| ^ {2 k} | \\alpha_ {j} | ^ {2} = \\left| \\frac {\\lambda_ {2}}{\\lambda_ {1}} \\right| ^ {2 k} \\left(| \\alpha_ {2} | ^ {2} + \\sum_ {j = 3} ^ {m} \\left| \\frac {\\lambda_ {j}}{\\lambda_ {2}} \\right| ^ {2 k} | \\alpha_ {j} | ^ {2}\\right),\n\\]"
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "bbox": [
                0.113,
                0.537,
                0.178,
                0.553
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "similarly"
        },
        {
            "type": "equation",
            "bbox": [
                0.297,
                0.55,
                0.641,
                0.597
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "\\[\n\\left| \\left| e ^ {(k + 1)} \\right| \\right| ^ {2} = \\left| \\frac {\\lambda_ {2}}{\\lambda_ {1}} \\right| ^ {2 (k + 1)} \\left(\\left| \\alpha_ {2} \\right| ^ {2} + \\sum_ {j = 3} ^ {m} \\left| \\frac {\\lambda_ {j}}{\\lambda_ {2}} \\right| ^ {2 (k + 1)} \\left| \\alpha_ {j} \\right| ^ {2}\\right).\n\\]"
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "bbox": [
                0.114,
                0.599,
                0.153,
                0.612
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "Thus"
        },
        {
            "type": "equation",
            "bbox": [
                0.223,
                0.617,
                0.715,
                0.762
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "\\[\n\\begin{array}{l} \\lim  _ {k \\rightarrow \\infty} \\frac {\\left|\\left| e ^ {(k + 1)} \\right|\\right|}{\\left|\\left| e ^ {(k)} \\right|\\right|} = \\lim  _ {k \\rightarrow \\infty} \\left(\\frac {\\left| \\frac {\\lambda_ {2}}{\\lambda_ {1}} \\right| ^ {2 (k + 1)} \\left(| \\alpha_ {2} | ^ {2} + \\sum_ {j = 3} ^ {m} \\left| \\frac {\\lambda_ {j}}{\\lambda_ {2}} \\right| ^ {2 (k + 1)} | \\alpha_ {j} | ^ {2}\\right)}{\\left| \\frac {\\lambda_ {2}}{\\lambda_ {1}} \\right| ^ {2 k} \\left(| \\alpha_ {2} | ^ {2} + \\sum_ {j = 3} ^ {m} \\left| \\frac {\\lambda_ {j}}{\\lambda_ {2}} \\right| ^ {2 k} | \\alpha_ {j} | ^ {2}\\right)}\\right) ^ {\\frac {1}{2}} \\\\ = \\left| \\frac {\\lambda_ {2}}{\\lambda_ {1}} \\right| \\frac {| \\alpha_ {2} |}{| \\alpha_ {2} |} \\quad (\\text {w e h a v e u s e d} | \\lambda_ {2} | > | \\lambda_ {3} | \\geq | \\lambda_ {j} | \\text {f o r} j > 3) \\\\ = \\left| \\frac {\\lambda_ {2}}{\\lambda_ {1}} \\right| \\quad (\\text {s i n c e} \\alpha_ {2} \\neq 0). \\\\ \\end{array}\n\\]"
        },
